JEFFREY HUSTON is a Seattle based guitarist, composer and improvisor. Most
recently, he collaborated in the creation and performance of Degenerate Art
Ensemble's "Sonic Tales," which premiered at Seattle's Moore Theater Halloween
weekend, 2009. He has created and performed scores to accompany choreography
by Amelia Reeber, Paige Barnes, John and Anna Dixon, Peggy Piacenza, Northwest
Dance Syndrome and Alia Swersky. He is currently exploring the expressive
potential of sound in a variety of contexts including the group Dead Hot, as
well as his own investigations in song writing and software based instrument
design and implementation. Jeff holds a Bachelors of Music from Cornish
College of the Arts. Find out more at www.jeffreyalanhuston.com.